=== Festivals ===
List of annual festivals held at Katsuragi Hitokotonushi Shrine<ref name="由緒書"/>.
* New Year’s Day Festival (January 1)
* Setsubun Festival (around February 3)
* Spring Grand Festival (April 5)
* Inari Shrine Festival (May 3)
* Summer Purification Festival (June 30)
* Autumn Grand Festival (Sacred Fire Festival) (September 15)
* Zako Festival (second Sunday of October)
* Ichiyō Raifuku Festival (winter solstice)

=== Appearances in works ===
* {{ill|lt=Matsuo Bashō|Q5676|qid=Q5676|1=Matsuo Bashō}} *Oi no Kobumi*{{Sfn|葛木坐一言主神社（神々）|1985年}}
*: {{Cquote|{{small|As I made a pilgrimage through the land of Yamato and passed the foot of Mount Katsuragi, flowers were in full bloom on all sides, the peaks veiled in haze—at dawn the scenery was all the more alluring. Hearing people speak ill of the appearance of that god,}}<br /> Still I longed to see—through flowers, the dawning face of the god|20px||*Oi no Kobumi*}}

